# Hyper-Casual — Project Configuration

## Project Overview
- **Unity Version:** 2022.3 LTS
- **Render Pipeline:** URP (mobile optimized)
- **Genre:** Hyper-casual (one-tap / swipe)
- **Target Platform:** iOS + Android
- **Target FPS:** 30 (battery-friendly)

## Architecture

### Assembly Structure
```
MyGame.Core         — events, pooling, utilities
MyGame.Gameplay     — game mechanic, obstacles, scoring
MyGame.UI           — menu, game over, score display
MyGame.Systems      — audio, save, ads, analytics
```

### Key Systems
- **Game Loop** — Menu → Playing → GameOver → Menu (instant transitions)
- **One-Tap Input** — single touch = primary action
- **Scoring** — distance/time/collectibles based
- **Level Progression** — config-driven difficulty ramping
- **Monetization** — interstitial (every 3rd death), rewarded (continue/2x), banner (menu only)
- **Analytics** — level_start, level_complete, ad_watched, retention events

### Scene Structure
- `S_Bootstrap` — persistent services (audio, ads, analytics)
- `S_Game` — single scene for everything (menu is overlay UI)

## Skills to Load
- `mobile` — ASTC textures, draw call budget, thermal management, safe areas
- `hyper-casual` — one-tap controls, level progression, monetization hooks
- `object-pooling` — pool everything that spawns
- `state-machine` — game state management
- `audio` — compressed audio, pooled sources

## Rules
Follow all rules in `.codex-legacy/rules/`.

## Key Conventions
- **< 30 draw calls** — trivially simple rendering
- **< 50MB build size** — critical for ad network CPI
- **Solid colors, no textures** — primitives with materials
- **30fps** — saves battery, users don't notice
- **Instant retry** — no confirmation dialogs, no delays
- **Pool everything** — zero runtime Instantiate/Destroy
- **No tutorial screen** — mechanic is self-evident in 3 seconds
- **Safe area** — all UI respects Screen.safeArea

## Input Map
```
Player:
  Tap — Primary Touch (press)
  Hold — Primary Touch (hold)
  Swipe — Touch Delta (if applicable)
```

## MCP Integration
Unity MCP at `http://localhost:8080/mcp`. Use for scene setup and build configuration.
